{"type":"assistant","message":{"model":"claude-sonnet-4-6","id":"msg_019J8SvZE6ZKupEZ6RKurB34","type":"message","role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"thinking","thinking":"The error still references `/tmp/ray/session_2026-06-16_01-19-09_068848_13` even after deleting `/tmp/ray`. This session path is being retrieved from the GCS server (from the ray-head cluster). When the client connects to the GCS at ray-head:6379, it gets the session info from the head node. The `node_ip_address.json` file is supposed to be on the head node, not on the client pod.\n\nThis looks like a fundamental issue with how the Ray client pod is trying to connect. In Ray, when you connect with `address='ray-head:6379'`, you're creating a \"driver\" node that connects to the cluster GCS. \n\nThe client then tries to find a matching local session file, but this only works if it's running on the head node itself or using the Ray Client protocol on port 10001. Since that port isn't exposed by the service—only 6379 and 8265 are available—I need to check what the ray-client pod's connection configuration actually expects.","signature":""}],"stop_reason":null,"stop_sequence":null,"stop_details":null,"usage":{"input_tokens":1,"cache_creation_input_tokens":1703,"cache_read_input_tokens":31102,"cache_creation":{"ephemeral_5m_input_tokens":0,"ephemeral_1h_input_tokens":1703},"output_tokens":38,"service_tier":"standard","inference_geo":"not_available"},"diagnostics":null,"context_management":null},"parent_tool_use_id":null,"session_id":"0b49470a-2432-424f-a1d2-62c13d3779cb","uuid":"dbafe148-2aa2-47f1-bcf5-b8f775d0cbb1","request_id":"req_011Cc6cjbD2AgYGKDCoUrC37"}
